article.description: Texas-San Antonio tops No. Arizona in OT 88-83
article.headline: Texas-San Antonio tops No. Arizona in OT 88-83
article.linkText: Texas-San Antonio tops No. Arizona in OT 88-83
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Keon Lewis scored 22 points and Texas San Antonio topped Northern Arizona in overtime 88-83 on Wednesday. Lewis and Jeromie Hill, who finished with 16 points, combined for 12 points in the extra session. San Antonio led 72-69 with 46 seconds left on Lewis' layup, but on the next possession Aaseem Dixon nailed a 3-pointer to tie it. Quinton Upshur's 3-point attempt at the buzzer for Northern Arizona missed and it went to overtime. The game was tied at 11 early on, but Northern Arizona went on a 13-2 run -- highlighted by a pair of 3-pointers by Dixon -- and led 44-35 at the break. UTSA scored the first 10 points of the second half to get back into the game. Dixon finished with career-highs in points (31), 3-pointers made (9) and attempts (19). Upshur had 17 points but was 1 of 11 on 3-pointers.
